methods.name: boolean isReadOnly()
methods.comment:
* Returns the value of the read-only attribute. * *

This attribute is often used as a simple access control mechanism * to prevent files from being deleted or updated. Whether the file system * or platform does any enforcement to prevent read-only files * from being updated is implementation specific. * * @return the value of the read-only attribute

methods.name: boolean isHidden()
methods.comment:
* Returns the value of the hidden attribute. * *

This attribute is often used to indicate if the file is visible to * users. * * @return the value of the hidden attribute

methods.name: boolean isArchive()
methods.comment:
* Returns the value of the archive attribute. * *

This attribute is typically used by backup programs. * * @return the value of the archive attribute

methods.name: boolean isSystem()
methods.comment:
* Returns the value of the system attribute. * *

This attribute is often used to indicate that the file is a component * of the operating system. * * @return the value of the system attribute
